  <h2>What Each Typically Means</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Pumping.</strong> Generally removing the liquid and accessible contents from the tank.</li>
    <li><strong>Cleaning.</strong> Generally a more thorough removal of the settled sludge from each compartment.</li>
    <li><strong>Why it matters.</strong> A tank that looks pumped can still hold a compacted sludge layer.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What to Confirm</h2>
  <p>
    When you request service, confirm which scope a quote covers so expectations match. If you are unsure which you need, describe the situation and let the provider advise. See <a href="/septic-tank-cleaning-cookeville-tn/">septic tank cleaning</a>, or <a href="/request-service/">request septic service</a>.
  </p>

